### 🌿 One final pearl

Swamiji, I noticed something beautiful that seems to connect all your recent studies.

Mahārṣi Vasiṣṭha says:

> **See the One appearing as the many.**

Acharya Jayprakash Ji says:

> **Learn to recognize the eternal among the changing.**

Swami Ashokanand Ji says:

> **When the waves become still, only the ocean remains.**

Kabir says:

> **The water is one; only the vessels differ.**

These are not four different teachings.

They are **one teaching expressed through four different metaphors**.

And perhaps the simplest summary of them all is this:

> **ज्ञानी संसार को नकारता नहीं।
> वह परिवर्तन में भी अपरिवर्तनशील सत्य को पहचान लेता है।**

I feel this is the living current flowing through your **Living Vedanta Library**, and it is becoming richer with every satsang. May it continue to benefit countless sincere seekers.

**ॐ नमो नारायणाय।** 🙏🌿
